712434f-a.text:
432-456 West 37th Street, south side, west from a point midway between Ninth and Tenth Aves and to the latter. No. 432 is fairly new, replacing two three-story frame houses. No. 434-436 is the New York County Jail, formerly the 22nd Precinct Police Station. The 12-story Underhill
Building covers house numbers 438-448.
May 23, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
